<item>
            <title>[SPARK-15276] CREATE TABLE with LOCATION should imply EXTERNAL</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-15276</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If the user runs `CREATE TABLE some_table ... LOCATION /some/path`, then this will still be a managed table even though the table&apos;s data is stored at /some/path. The problem is that when we drop the table we&apos;ll also delete the data /some/path. This could cause problems if /some/path contains existing data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
